## DaaS App-Sec Governance & DevSecOps Platform Manual
DevSecOps-as-a-Service (DaaS) eliminates the operational overhead of managing local software build setups, infrastructure hosting, tool updates, and telemetry tracing. This centralized NetApp framework allows product groups to dispatch compliant deployments rapidly while embedding deep security gates at every execution phase.
------------------------------
## 1. Supported Platform Ecosystem Integrations
DaaS abstracts security configurations using official plug-ins, custom dynamic agents, and centralized credential mappings across the following tools:

* Source Code Management (SCM): Perforce (BigTop Cluster), Bitbucket (BigTop & OpenLab), and GitHub (OpenLab).
* Artifact Operations: SonarQube, JFrog Artifactory registries (Docker & Helm), and Tenable Nessus networks.
* Security & Vulnerability Analysis: Coverity SAST and Synopsys Detect / Black Duck SCA.

------------------------------
## 2. Synopsys Detect (Black Duck) SCA Integration
The Synopsys Detect for Jenkins Plugin comes pre-installed across the DaaS cluster to run compositional analysis scans, build dependency Bill of Materials (BOM) inventories, flag license violations, and identify open-source security vulnerabilities.
## 2.1. Server Deployment Tiers

* Production Deployment Instance: https://blackduck.eng.netapp.com
* Staging Verification Instance: https://blackduck-staging.eng.netapp.com
* Account Creation Workflow: Open an engineering request ticket with enghelp+blackduck@netapp.com to generate your targeted project workspace.

## 2.2. Black Duck User Role Mapping Matrix

| Assigned User Role | Operational Action Scope |
|---|---|
| Project Creator | Generates parent Black Duck projects. |
| Project Code Scanner | Populates the local project Bill of Materials (BOM). |
| Global Code Scanner | Populates the project BOM, awaits parsing metrics, compiles vulnerability compliance reports, and checks for explicit corporate policy violations. |
| Project Manager | Extracts and downloads compliance report data packages. |

## 2.3. Plugin Configuration Lifecycle
Configure your master plugin connection via Manage Jenkins ➔ Configure System ➔ Synopsys Detect:

   1. Global Download Strategy: Choose Install AirGapped Detect as a Tool Installation (SecLab) for highly secure execution profiles, or Download via scripts / use DETECT_JAR (Open EngLab) for open network zones.
   2. Black Duck URL: Input your designated server endpoint instance.
   3. Black Duck Credentials: Click Add ➔ Jenkins.
   * For API Tokens: Change the Kind dropdown to Secret text and paste your secure Black Duck access token within the Secret text area.
      * For Basic Authentication: Select Username with password.
   4. Advanced Settings: Adjust the Connection Timeout boundary if necessary (defaults to 120 seconds). Select Trust Black Duck certificates to allow Secure Socket Layer (SSL) verification handshakes.
   5. Click Test Connection to Black Duck to verify configuration alignment, then click Save.

## 2.4. Pipeline Workflow Generation
To append compositional scanning steps into your Jenkinsfile workflow scripts, utilize the embedded Pipeline Syntax helper utility:

   1. Click the Pipeline Syntax navigation link on any active Jenkins pipeline item view.
   2. Under the Sample Step dropdown selector block, choose synopsys_detect: Synopsys Detect.
   3. Append your targeted evaluation properties inside the arguments block window.
   4. (Optional) Select Return status code or enforce a Custom download strategy toggle box.
   5. Click Generate Pipeline Script and paste the resulting statement loop directly into your declarative script block.

